  "text": "The ability of L.s.-P and its fractions to modulate angiogenesis in vitro was evaluated in a capillary tube formation (tubulogenesis) assay as previously reported [CITATION_1] . Briefly, chamber slides were coated with growth factor-depleted Matrigel (BD Pharmingen) for 1 h at 37uC. HUVECs resuspended in M199 containing 10% FBS were seeded on Matrigel (5610 Plasminogen Activator Inhibitor-1 (PAI-1) antigen assay Levels of PAI-1 antigen were measured in conditioned media (CM) from HUVECs plated on Matrigel for the tubulogenesis assay in the presence or absence of L.s.-P or its fractions. After 20 h of incubation, CM were collected, centrifuged and stored. Five ml of CM were used for the measurement of PAI-1 using an enzyme-linked immunosorbent assays (ELISAs) (American Diagnostica GmbH, Germany).",
